item.title: What's Next for Kyle Liao
item.description: I’m writing this 10 days after winning a hackathon. It’s surreal. As Sahib said, it was like a 48 hour fever dream. It all started from just one day. The right place the right time kind of situation. I was checking hackathons.hackclub.com to find hackathons. Nothing new. I went to check MLH.io hackathons and found it. HackPHS, in Princeton NJ for High School students. I clicked on the website to make sure it was a date and time I could attend.

item.title: Project Diani at Code Overflow22(BIG W)
item.description: Project Diani was a 24 hour hackathon project based off of Arduino, which was written in C++ where my main job was creating the documentation and the website for it. The team was composed off our lead C++ dev, Sahib, along with Batuhuan as C++ assist, and Dorian our overall designer, and me as our front end. 9:00 AM We arrive at 9 AM and enter. The opening talk starts at 10.
